    "content_hash": "64c3cf6cb54a7732",
    "department": "Enterprise Technology",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE MATTERS\n\nAt Snowflake, our collaboration and identity platforms power a global, cloud-first workforce. We’re looking for a hands-on engineer who can scale, secure, and intelligently automate our enterprise collaboration ecosystem across Okta, Google Workspace, Slack, and PagerDuty.\n\nIf you thrive on automation, identity architecture, SaaS integrations, and building systems that eliminate manual work — this role is for you.\n\n\nAS A CLOUD DEVOPS ENGINEER, YOU WILL:\n\n - Own and optimise enterprise collaboration platforms (Okta, IGA/IAM, Google Workspace, Slack, PagerDuty).\n\n - Design and automate identity lifecycle processes (SCIM \u0026 non-SCIM provisioning).\n\n - Architect secure SSO integrations (SAML/OAuth/OIDC), MFA policies, RBAC, and access governance.\n\n - Build scalable automation frameworks using Python/PowerShell/Bash and REST APIs.\n\n - Develop lightweight services or serverless workflows (e.g., AWS Lambda) to enable event-driven integrations.\n\n - Integrate with SaaS platforms like ServiceNow.\n\n - Lead security remediation and compliance hardening initiatives.\n\n - Apply DevOps best practices (CI/CD, Git, monitoring, configuration management).\n\n - Drive AI-first automation strategies to eliminate repetitive operational tasks.\n\n - Partner cross-functionally with Security, Compliance, Engineering, and IT.\n\n\nOUR IDEAL CANDIDATE WILL HAVE MOST OF THE FOLLOWING QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - 5–7 years managing enterprise collaboration and IAM platforms.\n\n - Deep expertise in Okta (SSO, MFA, lifecycle, SCIM, custom integrations, API automation).\n\n - Strong knowledge of Google Workspace, Slack, and PagerDuty\n\n - Strong knowledge of IAM principles and authentication flows.\n\n - Strong scripting and API integration skills.\n\n - Experience designing scalable SaaS onboarding frameworks.\n\n - Cloud experience (GCP required; AWS/Azure a plus).\n\n - Ownership mindset with strong troubleshooting and analytical skills.\n\n\nGOOD TO HAVE\n\n - ServiceNow automation experience\n\n - Infrastructure-as-Code exposure\n\n - Snowflake platform familiarity\n\n - Relevant certifications (Okta, Google Workspace, IAM, Cloud)\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
